                <h2>Tissue Culture Sequence <span class="punjabi">(ਟਿਸ਼ੂ ਕਲਚਰ)</span></h2>
                <p><strong>Interactive Sequencer:</strong> Build the process of micropropagation.</p>
                <div class="sequencer-container" id="seq-ch7-1">
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>1. Extraction:</strong> A small piece of tissue is removed from the growing tip of a plant.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>2. Culture Medium:</strong> It is placed in an artificial jelly medium containing nutrients.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>3. Callus Formation:</strong> The cells divide rapidly to form an unorganized mass called a <span class="exam-keyword">Callus</span>.
                    </div>
                    <div class="seq-step">
                        <strong>4. Hormonal Transfer:</strong> The callus is transferred to another medium with hormones to trigger root and shoot growth.
